        <h3>4. Technical and Organisational Security Measures</h3>

        <h3>Security Management System</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>The Organization maintains a documented information security management system (ISMS) aligned with ISO 27001:2013 and ISO 27701:2019.</li>
          <li>Policies and procedures are reviewed at least annually and updated to reflect changes in the regulatory and threat landscape.</li>
          <li>A dedicated Data Protection Officer (DPO) oversees compliance with GDPR and other applicable Data Protection Laws.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Personnel Security</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>All employees and contractors undergo background checks prior to engagement.</li>
          <li>Staff receive regular training on data protection obligations, information security awareness, and incident response procedures.</li>
          <li>Confidentiality agreements are signed by all personnel with access to Client Personal Data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Access Controls</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Access to Client Personal Data is restricted on a need-to-know basis using role-based access controls (RBAC).</li>
          <li>Multi-factor authentication (MFA) is enforced for all systems that process Client Personal Data.</li>
          <li>Access rights are reviewed quarterly and promptly revoked upon role change or termination.</li>
          <li>Privileged access is logged and monitored.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Data Center and Network Security</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Client Personal Data is processed and stored within facilities located in the EU (The Hague Region, Netherlands) unless otherwise specified.</li>
          <li>Data in transit is protected using TLS 1.2 or higher encryption.</li>
          <li>Data at rest is encrypted using AES-256 or equivalent standards.</li>
          <li>Network segmentation, firewalls, and intrusion detection/prevention systems (IDS/IPS) are in place.</li>
          <li>Regular vulnerability assessments and penetration testing are conducted at least annually.</li>
          <li>Automated monitoring and alerting systems are deployed for anomaly detection.</li>
          <li>Backup and disaster recovery plans are maintained and tested regularly to ensure availability and resilience of processing systems.</li>
        </ul>

